# ESP32-Based IoT Environmental Monitoring System

## 1. Abstract

The ESP32-Based IoT Environmental Monitoring System is designed to monitor environmental parameters in real time using multiple sensors and cloud connectivity. The system utilizes an ESP32 microcontroller interfaced with DHT22, MQ-2 Gas Sensor, Soil Moisture Sensor, and HC-SR04 Ultrasonic Sensor to collect data related to temperature, humidity, gas concentration, soil moisture, and water level. The collected data is transmitted to the Blynk cloud platform through Wi-Fi, enabling remote monitoring using a mobile application.

This project demonstrates the integration of IoT technologies for environmental monitoring and smart automation applications.

---

## 2. Objectives

* To monitor environmental conditions in real time.
* To enable remote monitoring using IoT technology.
* To collect data from multiple sensors using ESP32.
* To visualize sensor readings through the Blynk dashboard.
* To improve safety through gas leakage and water-level monitoring.

---

## 3. Problem Statement

Manual monitoring of environmental parameters is time-consuming and inefficient, especially in agricultural, industrial, and smart home environments. There is a need for a low-cost IoT-based solution that continuously monitors environmental conditions and provides real-time data access from remote locations.

